getName

public java.lang.String getName()
The name attribute is used to store a single string token that represents a unique name for an object. A name should be composed of characters in the range, [a-z] [A-Z] [0-9]. No whitespace characters are allowed. All names must start with a character.

getAttachToClass

public java.util.Iterator<ClassDefinitionREF> getAttachToClass()
Indicates the classes of object to which an action is to be attached. This mechanism allows for the extension of a class's behaviour without having to alter the schema of the class involved. This can be viewed as the auxiliary class equivalent for behaviour.

An Iterator of ClassDefinitionDMO objects.

getBlockWhenLocked

public java.lang.Boolean getBlockWhenLocked()
This flag indicates whether or not an Action will be blocked from proceeding if there is a DAF lock on the object against which the action is performed. The default is to block all incoming actions against a locked object. By setting this flag to false, you can allow an action to proceed.

getIsGetAction

public java.lang.Boolean getIsGetAction()
This flag indicates if an Action is merely a data retrieval (get) Action. Actions that are flagged with this attribute set to true will be executable even when the server is in a read-only mode because they don't actually alter data. One example of this is the getAllowedOperations() action on the SecurityBranch.

getObsoleteVersion

public java.lang.String getObsoleteVersion()
This indicates the version at which something became obsolete. Generally speaking you shouldn't ever delete definitions for products that have been released to the field, this may break backwards compatibility. Instead, you should mark them as obsolete.

getMaySendProgress

public java.lang.Boolean getMaySendProgress()
This flag is used to indicate if a particular request might result in progress indications being sent. Although primarily intended as a documentation aspect, this flag is used within the TL1 subsystem to allow for the creation of a response handler for node requests that send progress text.
